{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nThe GitHub CodeQL \"Security and quality\" scan flags `py/clear-text-logging-sensitive-data` in\n`docs/experiments/workflow-remediation-pocs/runtime_pydanticai_poc.py` (code-scanning alerts 3 and 4).\nThat file is a hand-run proof-of-concept: it is not packaged (the wheel/sdist ship only `src/rebar` —\n`pyproject.toml:213`), is on no `import rebar` path, and never runs in production. The findings are\nfalse positives (they log public provider-name strings such as \"anthropic\"/\"openai\", not secrets). The\nindividual alerts have been dismissed, but any code under `docs/` keeps generating recurring scan noise\non every push. The advanced-setup CodeQL workflow (`.github/workflows/codeql.yml`) currently passes no\nconfig, so nothing is excluded.\n\n## What\nAdd a CodeQL config file that excludes `docs/**` from analysis and wire it into the workflow, so the\nexclusion is durable (survives future `docs/experiments` additions) rather than relying on per-alert\ndismissals.\n- New file `.github/codeql/codeql-config.yml` with `paths-ignore: [\"docs/**\"]`.\n- Edit `.github/workflows/codeql.yml`: pass `config-file: ./.github/codeql/codeql-config.yml` to the\n  `github/codeql-action/init` step. No change to the default query suite (only path scoping).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `.github/codeql/codeql-config.yml` exists and its `paths-ignore` list covers `docs/**`.\n- [ ] The CodeQL workflow `init` step (`.github/workflows/codeql.yml`) references that config via `config-file:`.\n- [ ] `python -c \"import yaml,sys; d=yaml.safe_load(open('.github/codeql/codeql-config.yml')); assert 'docs/**' in d['paths-ignore']\"` exits 0 (config parses and contains the exclusion).\n- [ ] No file under `src/rebar` is modified in this change (config/workflow only, so no runtime behavior change) — verified by `git diff --name-only origin/main` listing only `.github/` paths.\n\n## Verification\n- `python -c \"import yaml; yaml.safe_load(open('.github/codeql/codeql-config.yml'))\"` — config is valid YAML.\n- `grep -q 'config-file: ./.github/codeql/codeql-config.yml' .github/workflows/codeql.yml` — wiring present.\n- `git diff --name-only origin/main` — shows only `.github/codeql/codeql-config.yml` and `.github/workflows/codeql.yml`.\n\n## Out of scope\n- The 27 valid `py/path-injection` findings and the `py/stack-trace-exposure` finding (alert 27): those\n  need real code fixes and are tracked separately."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784350106681922001,"uuid":"d79915da-c3ab-44d3-ac06-6939ad740fa8"}